sn16.11:4.3:
"In the past, friend, when I was still a householder, it occurred to me: ‘Household life is confinement, a path of dust, going forth is like the open air. It is not easy for one living at home to lead the perfectly complete, perfectly purified holy life, which is like polished conch. Let me then shave off my hair and beard, put on saffron robes, and go forth from the household life into homelessness. ’ Some time later
I had an outer robe made from patches of cloth;
then, acknowledging those who were arahants in the world (as models), I shaved off my hair and beard, put on saffron robes, and went forth from the household life into homelessness.
